POLOKWANE – Partial sunshine, mostly sunny and warm conditions are what residents in the city can expect weather-wise this week. AccuWeather’s forecast suggests high temperatures and partly cloudy conditions throughout the week. Maximum temperatures will range between 28ºC and 31ºC so it would be best to stay hydrated and wear a hat and sunscreen if you are venturing outside.  Thursday and Saturday will be the hottest days of the week, peaking at 31ºC with little to no rain expected. The only chance of rain is a 40% chance of a stray morning thundershower on Tuesday (March 7), while the rest of the week will remain dry. There is, however, a 25% chance of rain on Friday (March 10). Minimum temperatures will remain in the mid to high teens. 